    Text only  & 86.1 & 94.0 & 92.3 & 85.0 \\
    Image only & 84.8 & 90.7 & 91.5 & \textbf{86.0} \\
    \rowcolor{blue!8} \textbf{Both (Ours)} & \textbf{87.3} & \textbf{94.7} & \textbf{92.3} & 84.0 \\
    \bottomrule
    \end{tabular}

    \vspace{0.4em}
    {\footnotesize \textit{Both} achieves best or competitive SR on every dataset. Text dominates for nudity (explicit keywords); image catches adversarial prompts that avoid unsafe vocabulary (MJA-Sexual: image 86.0 $>$ text 85.0).}
